My neighbours have installed fancy new lights in their garden – not for security, mind, but for mood. However, these lights are somewhat … dazzling. Their small lawn is now a floodlit tennis court for fairies, their path a landing strip. When I go to bed, beams of white stripe my bedroom ceiling. These lights can be seen from actual space. Mercifully, I have heavy curtains, but here’s my problem: insects do not. Night creatures do not. Birds do not. Yes, maybe I’m exaggerating a little (they aren’t visible from space) but how do I tell my lovely neighbours to...